  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Chop your <strong>sweet potato[es]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel your <strong>parsnip[s]</strong>, then continue to peel lengths until you end up with a few parsnip ribbons</p><p>Dice the <strong>remaining parsnip[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1702994276318-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1702994276318-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1702994276318-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1702994276318-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1702994276318-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>chopped sweet potato </strong>and <strong>butternut squash cubes</strong> on one side of a baking tray with the <strong>diced parsnip </strong>and <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong></p><p>Add a little drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 20 min or until tender – this is your <strong>smoky roast veg</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1702994279575-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1702994279575-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1702994279575-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1702994279575-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1702994279575-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic cloves</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife and discard the skins</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1702994282434-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1702994282434-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1702994282434-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1702994282434-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1702994282434-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pot with a little drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>onion wedges</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Meanwhile, chop your<strong> potato[es] </strong>into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Top, tail and chop your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> roughly</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1702994286427-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1702994286427-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1702994286427-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1702994286427-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1702994286427-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has slightly softened, add your <strong>curry powder</strong> and <strong>tomato paste </strong>with the <strong>crushed garlic </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chopped potato</strong> and <strong>carrots </strong>with 800ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[1L]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.3L] </span><strong>boiled water</strong>, your<strong> creamed coconut </strong>and <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong></p><p>Bring to a boil over a high heat, then reduce the heat to medium and cook for 15 min or until the potato is tender – this is your <strong>soup base</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1702994289769-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1702994289769-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1702994289769-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1702994289769-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1702994289769-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the smoky roast veg has had an initial 20 min, remove the tray from the oven and add the <strong>parsnip ribbons </strong>in rows with a little drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use a separate tray!</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for 3-5 min or until the ribbons are crisp</p><p>Once the ribbons are crisp, remove the tray[s] from the oven and set aside – this is your <strong>smoky roast veg </strong>and<strong> parsnip crisps</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1702994294168-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1702994294168-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1702994294168-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1702994294168-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1702994294168-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are tender, remove the pot from the heat and blitz with a <strong>(stick) blender</strong> until smooth</p><p>Once smooth, add the<strong> smoky roast veg </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> – this is your <strong>curried winter veg soup</strong></p><p>Slice your<strong> ciabatta[s] </strong>in half and place in the toaster for 1-2 min or until toasted, then slice into triangles</p><p>Tip: For a little extra indulgence, butter the ciabatta once toasted!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1702994296679-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1702994296679-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1702994296679-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1702994296679-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1702994296679-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>curried winter veg soup </strong>and drizzle over your<strong> natural yoghurt</strong></p><p>Top with the<strong> parsnip crisps </strong>and a grind of<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> toasted ciabatta triangles </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
